body:
During  `pipeline.run()`, the normalization step can create variant columns to avoid incompatible types in the destination (e.g., trying to write a `string` to a `boolean` column)

It seems to only propagate the `nullable` hint (and set `data_type`, `variant`). It would add clarity to add a default `description` "Variant of column `{column_name}` generated by dlt"

<img width="1132" height="750" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d43d357c-6a36-4726-b8d3-74d959729655" />

```json
{
  "tables": {
    "TABLE": {
      "columns": {
        "metric_value": {
          "name": "metric_value",
          "data_type": "bigint",
          "description": "Value of the metric",
          "nullable": true,
          "variant": true
        },
        "metric_value__v_text": {
          "name": "metric_value__v_text",
          "data_type": "text",
          "nullable": true,
          "variant": true
        },
        "metric_value__v_double": {
          "name": "metric_value__v_double",
          "data_type": "double",
          "nullable": true,
          "variant": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
